{"build_type":"executable","description":"Fail-closed combined request-tool contract auditor. Given roots, enumerates the package universe, builds the function index, derives the set of request-taking command tools (executable packages whose closure reaches the single sanctioned request entry), then checks two contracts over that derived set: every such tool must reach the single sanctioned output emitter, and every such tool must reach the unknown-parameter rejection helper. Emits the two missing counts, the offending entry lists, and a catalog code when any violation exists, returning the combined violation count as the exit status so a build gate fails closed when any request tool can exit without emitting or accept unknown parameters silently.","module_name":"report-request-protocols-missing-output-guard","package_name":"report-request-protocols-missing-output-guard","function_definitions":{"report-request-protocols-missing-output-guard":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c24","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":24},{"instruction_type":"variable_